<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="117" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,258,967]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,258,283]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anterior dorsum yellow with black marks. Crown (
<figureCitation box="[872,955,258,283]" captionStart="FIGURES 75 – 84" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1583,1606]" captionTargetBox="[152,1416,203,1557]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,193,1563]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 75 – 84. (75 – 77) Apogonalia pennata Nielson &amp; Godoy, 1995, female: 75, dorsal habitus; 76, sternite VII, ventral view; 77, sternite VIII, dorsal view. (78 – 82) A. pinguis Young, 1977, female: 78, dorsal habitus; 79, left forewing, lateral view; 80, sternite VII, ventral view; 81, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 82, pygofer, lateral view. (83 – 84) A. robusta (Walker, 1851), female: 83, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 84, pygofer, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035600/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Fig. 78</figureCitation>
) with six large black marks, two pairs on anterior margin, one pair between ocelli. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[750,833,294,319]" captionStart="FIGURES 75 – 84" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1583,1606]" captionTargetBox="[152,1416,203,1557]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,193,1563]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 75 – 84. (75 – 77) Apogonalia pennata Nielson &amp; Godoy, 1995, female: 75, dorsal habitus; 76, sternite VII, ventral view; 77, sternite VIII, dorsal view. (78 – 82) A. pinguis Young, 1977, female: 78, dorsal habitus; 79, left forewing, lateral view; 80, sternite VII, ventral view; 81, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 82, pygofer, lateral view. (83 – 84) A. robusta (Walker, 1851), female: 83, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 84, pygofer, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035600/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Fig. 78</figureCitation>
) with pair of anterolateral black maculae adjacent to eyes; disc with two pairs of narrow longitudinal black stripes. Mesonotum (
<figureCitation box="[998,1080,330,355]" captionStart="FIGURES 75 – 84" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1583,1606]" captionTargetBox="[152,1416,203,1557]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,193,1563]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 75 – 84. (75 – 77) Apogonalia pennata Nielson &amp; Godoy, 1995, female: 75, dorsal habitus; 76, sternite VII, ventral view; 77, sternite VIII, dorsal view. (78 – 82) A. pinguis Young, 1977, female: 78, dorsal habitus; 79, left forewing, lateral view; 80, sternite VII, ventral view; 81, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 82, pygofer, lateral view. (83 – 84) A. robusta (Walker, 1851), female: 83, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 84, pygofer, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035600/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Fig. 78</figureCitation>
) with pair of longitudinal black stripes on mesoscutum. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[543,671,366,391]" captionStart="FIGURES 75 – 84" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1583,1606]" captionTargetBox="[152,1416,203,1557]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,193,1563]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 75 – 84. (75 – 77) Apogonalia pennata Nielson &amp; Godoy, 1995, female: 75, dorsal habitus; 76, sternite VII, ventral view; 77, sternite VIII, dorsal view. (78 – 82) A. pinguis Young, 1977, female: 78, dorsal habitus; 79, left forewing, lateral view; 80, sternite VII, ventral view; 81, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 82, pygofer, lateral view. (83 – 84) A. robusta (Walker, 1851), female: 83, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 84, pygofer, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035600/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Figs 78, 79</figureCitation>
) pinkish with narrow elongate black maculae on veins; corium with large elliptical black mark on outer discal cell; costal area anteriorly yellow; apical portion with two transverse blackish stripes. Face yellow with black marks. Frons with pair of elongate, mediolateral Y-shaped black marks; lateral margin with black stripe. Clypeus with median black stripe dorsally bifurcated. Aedeagal shaft with pair of ventroapical acute processes (
<bibRefCitation author="Young" box="[485,739,510,535]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" refString="Young, D. A. (1977) Taxonomic study of the Cicadellinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Part 2. New World Cicadellini and the genus Cicadella. Technical Bulletin of the North Carolina Agricultural Experiment Station, 239, 1 - 1135." type="journal article" year="1977" yearSuffix="f">Young 1977, fig. 747f</bibRefCitation>
). Female sternite VII (
<figureCitation box="[992,1074,510,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 75 – 84" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1583,1606]" captionTargetBox="[152,1416,203,1557]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,193,1563]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 75 – 84. (75 – 77) Apogonalia pennata Nielson &amp; Godoy, 1995, female: 75, dorsal habitus; 76, sternite VII, ventral view; 77, sternite VIII, dorsal view. (78 – 82) A. pinguis Young, 1977, female: 78, dorsal habitus; 79, left forewing, lateral view; 80, sternite VII, ventral view; 81, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 82, pygofer, lateral view. (83 – 84) A. robusta (Walker, 1851), female: 83, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 84, pygofer, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035600/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Fig. 80</figureCitation>
) with conspicuous central black macula; posterior margin with median concavity.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,258,967]" box="[199,548,582,607]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">
Female length. 
<quantity box="[372,458,583,607]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.3" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" unit="mm" value="8.3">8.3 mm</quantity>
(n = 1).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="117" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,258,967]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,576,618,643]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Description of female genitalia.</emphasis>
Sternite VII (
<figureCitation box="[736,820,618,643]" captionStart="FIGURES 75 – 84" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1583,1606]" captionTargetBox="[152,1416,203,1557]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,193,1563]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 75 – 84. (75 – 77) Apogonalia pennata Nielson &amp; Godoy, 1995, female: 75, dorsal habitus; 76, sternite VII, ventral view; 77, sternite VIII, dorsal view. (78 – 82) A. pinguis Young, 1977, female: 78, dorsal habitus; 79, left forewing, lateral view; 80, sternite VII, ventral view; 81, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 82, pygofer, lateral view. (83 – 84) A. robusta (Walker, 1851), female: 83, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 84, pygofer, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035600/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Fig. 80</figureCitation>
) similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freytag" authorityYear="2004" box="[1037,1159,619,642]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angusta">
<emphasis box="[1037,1159,619,642]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">A. angusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but with posteromedian concavity slightly narrower. Sternite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[655,743,654,679]" captionStart="FIGURES 75 – 84" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1583,1606]" captionTargetBox="[152,1416,203,1557]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,193,1563]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 75 – 84. (75 – 77) Apogonalia pennata Nielson &amp; Godoy, 1995, female: 75, dorsal habitus; 76, sternite VII, ventral view; 77, sternite VIII, dorsal view. (78 – 82) A. pinguis Young, 1977, female: 78, dorsal habitus; 79, left forewing, lateral view; 80, sternite VII, ventral view; 81, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 82, pygofer, lateral view. (83 – 84) A. robusta (Walker, 1851), female: 83, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 84, pygofer, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035600/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Fig. 81</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, with semilunar sclerotized plate; anterior margin of plate with pair of short lateral convex lobes. Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[868,949,690,715]" captionStart="FIGURES 75 – 84" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1583,1606]" captionTargetBox="[152,1416,203,1557]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,193,1563]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 75 – 84. (75 – 77) Apogonalia pennata Nielson &amp; Godoy, 1995, female: 75, dorsal habitus; 76, sternite VII, ventral view; 77, sternite VIII, dorsal view. (78 – 82) A. pinguis Young, 1977, female: 78, dorsal habitus; 79, left forewing, lateral view; 80, sternite VII, ventral view; 81, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 82, pygofer, lateral view. (83 – 84) A. robusta (Walker, 1851), female: 83, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 84, pygofer, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035600/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Fig. 82</figureCitation>
) with posterodorsal margin, in lateral view, broadly concave; disc with dorsal oblique row of long macrosetae, extending from central portion to posterodorsal margin, posteroventral portion with long macrosetae on apical half. Valvula I, in ventral view, with basal portion similar to that of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1794" box="[343,446,798,822]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="histrio">
<emphasis box="[343,446,798,822]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">A. histrio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; blade similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freytag" authorityYear="2004" box="[721,841,799,822]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angusta">
<emphasis box="[721,841,799,822]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">A. angusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Valvula II similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freytag" authorityYear="2004" box="[1164,1284,799,822]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angusta">
<emphasis box="[1164,1284,799,822]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">A. angusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; teeth spaced from one another about one tooth length on median portion; preapical prominence approximately aligned to anteapical tooth.
</paragraph>
